072 entries not only in Chinese characters and their Sino-Japanese (ondoku/onyomi) readings, but also the Japanese (kundoku/kunyomi) readings. The romanized Japanese readings will assist in correctly transcribing Japanese names, such as the names of Japanese publishers and authors, and the technical terms employed by Japanese in their writings on China. These features will also give those familiar with pinyin greater access to material on Japanese history and culture. The ABC Dictionary of Sino-Japanese Readings will be a boon to Sinologists and others interested in the study of China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 0aJapanese languagexPronunciationvDictionaries. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Chinese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package 2014-2016z978311056413608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082487224340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824872243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824872243.jpg  a978-3-11-056413-6  Hawaii eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles